==English==
{{wikipedia}}
===Etymology===
Ancient Greek [[Πλούτων]] (Plutōn)

===Pronunciation===
*:Rhymes: [[Rhymes:English:-uːtəʊ|-uːtəʊ]]

=== Proper noun ===
'''Pluto'''

# Greek and Roman [[god]] of the [[underworld]].
# The brightest and first known [[Kuiper belt object]], discovered in 1930, originally considered the ninth [[planet]] but now classified as a [[dwarf planet]], represented by the symbol {{Unicode|[[♇]]}}. Pluto and [[Charon]] form a [[tidally locked]] binary system in [[orbital resonance]] with [[Neptune]].

